---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Making Reachy Move"
  track="young-builders"
  week={5}
  phase="Phase 2: Reachy Basics"
  duration="60 min"
  emoji="🦾"
  objective="Control Reachy's arm and head movements with Python code"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-builder-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-builder-50 border-l-4 border-builder-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      You will understand robot coordinate systems, control Reachy's joints programmatically, and create a custom movement sequence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📚 Key Concepts</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-blue-700 mb-3">Joint Angles</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Robot arms move by rotating joints. Each joint has an angle measured in degrees:</p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
        <li>• <strong>0°</strong> = neutral position</li>
        <li>• <strong>+90°</strong> = 90 degrees one direction</li>
        <li>• <strong>-90°</strong> = 90 degrees the other direction</li>
        <li>• Reachy's shoulder can rotate ±90° and flex ±100°</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Your Body as a Robot (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Measure your own arm movements in degrees. Put your arm at your side = 0°. Raise it 45°, then 90°. Feel the difference. This is exactly how Reachy's motors work!</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Move Experiments (30 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Run the code below. Try different angles. Create a wave motion by looping through a sequence of angles. What's the difference between a fast move and a slow one?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Choreograph a Sequence (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Design a 6-step movement sequence. Give it a name. Save it as a function.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Reflection (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Write: what is the hardest movement to program? Why?</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># movement.py — Week 5: Young Builders
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def move_arm(self, arm, shoulder_angle, elbow_angle, speed=1.0):
        print(f"🦾 {arm} arm: shoulder={shoulder_angle}°, elbow={elbow_angle}° (speed={speed})")
        time.sleep(1.0 / speed)

    def move_head(self, pitch=0, yaw=0, roll=0):
        print(f"🤖 Head: pitch={pitch}°, yaw={yaw}°, roll={roll}°")
        time.sleep(0.5)

    def go_to_rest(self):
        print("😌 Moving to rest position")
        time.sleep(1)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()
    print("🎮 Simulator mode\n")

# Basic movements
robot.go_to_rest()

# Raise right arm
robot.move_arm("right", shoulder_angle=90, elbow_angle=0, speed=0.5)
time.sleep(0.5)

# Wave (loop through angles)
print("\n👋 Waving...")
for _ in range(3):
    robot.move_arm("right", shoulder_angle=90, elbow_angle=45, speed=2.0)
    robot.move_arm("right", shoulder_angle=90, elbow_angle=-45, speed=2.0)

robot.go_to_rest()

# Head movements
print("\n👀 Looking around...")
for direction, yaw in [("left", -30), ("center", 0), ("right", 30), ("center", 0)]:
    print(f"  → {direction}")
    robot.move_head(yaw=yaw)

# YOUR MOVEMENT SEQUENCE:
def my_sequence(robot):
    """Add your 6-step sequence here!"""
    pass

my_sequence(robot)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 How many degrees of freedom does Reachy's arm have? What about yours?</p></div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 Why does speed matter? When would slow movement be better than fast?</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 Coordinate systems and angle notation are also used in trigonometry and physics. Your child is building cross-curricular intuition!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
